      "id": "S3D09-Q016",
      "question": "During a fraud examination, Sarah discovers that her client's CEO has been making personal purchases with company funds. The CEO privately offers Sarah a substantial bonus to exclude these transactions from her final report. According to ethical principles governing fraud examiners, what should Sarah do?",
